{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"duration_ms":191931,"duration_api_ms":190047,"num_turns":19,"result":"","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"aea8e6d4-9724-48a5-b6d9-be7046b0808d","total_cost_usd":1.1618187500000001,"usage":{"input_tokens":19,"cache_creation_input_tokens":81323,"cache_read_input_tokens":908410,"output_tokens":7970,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":81323,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"},"modelUsage":{"claude-opus-4-6":{"inputTokens":19,"outputTokens":7970,"cacheReadInputTokens":908410,"cacheCreationInputTokens":81323,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":1.1618187500000001,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":64000}},"permission_denials":[],"structured_output":{"summary":"Reviewed the diff across model.rs, service.rs, and fs.rs. The changes refactor duplicate logic (same_attempt, merge_attempt_entries, collapse_task_run_attempts) into the model layer, make record_bead_start idempotent on retry, add duplicate-running-row repair in update_task_run, and de-duplicate journal events. All 73 milestone_record tests pass. The code correctly handles legacy paired rows, idempotent start retries, and terminal replay scenarios. Test coverage is thorough including edge cases (FailFirstJournalAppend, duplicate running rows, legacy terminal replay). No real bugs found; two minor robustness concerns noted below.","amendments":[{"body":"In `same_attempt` (model.rs:306-309), when exactly one side has a `run_id` and the other has `None`, the fallback compares `started_at`. If two distinct runs for the same bead/project happen to have identical `started_at` timestamps (e.g., sub-millisecond retry or clock coarseness), a start row with no run_id would incorrectly match both terminals. Consider adding a comment documenting this intentional trade-off for legacy compatibility, or tightening the fallback to also require that at least one side has `run_id == None` (which it already does via the wildcard arm, but the risk of false positives with identical timestamps is not documented).","rationale":"The `_ =>` wildcard arm fires for (Some, None) and (None, Some) AND (None, None). The (Some, None) case is the legacy pairing scenario and is intentional. But a reader unfamiliar with the legacy format could be confused about why run_id mismatch falls back to timestamp comparison. A brief doc comment would prevent future misunderstanding and make the edge-case risk explicit."},{"body":"In `record_bead_start` (service.rs:388-390), `existing_task_runs` is cloned twice — once for `collapse_task_run_attempts` and once for `reconcile_snapshot_from_lineage`. Since `reconcile_snapshot_from_lineage` internally calls `collapse_task_run_attempts` again, the collapse logic runs twice on the same data. Consider passing the already-collapsed `canonical_task_runs` into reconcile (changing its signature to accept pre-collapsed entries) or restructuring to avoid the redundant work.","rationale":"This is a performance concern, not a correctness bug. For large milestone histories the double clone + double collapse could become noticeable. The refactor would also simplify the function by making it clear that collapse happens exactly once."}]},"fast_mode_state":"off","uuid":"7c2dbea8-fa71-4cf5-a757-6606308a1fc7"}
